author: The Critical Drinker
description:
All right, we're all about the Sevens tonight as we talk about Akira Kurosawa's 1954 classic, and the (arguably better) all-star Western remake, and even the Roger Corman scifi spinoff from 1980. Join me and the Outcast Creative for Happy Hour! 

Subscribe to Outcast Creative: https://www.youtube.com/@THEOUTCASTSCREATIVE
Book tickets for Seven Magnificent Egos, the theatrical comedy about the trials and conflicts behind the scenes of Magnificent Seven: https://www.yeolderoseandcrowntheatrepub.co.uk/whats-on/7-magnificent-egos/about
title: Happy Hour - Seven Samurai, Magnificent Seven AND Battle Beyond The Stars

author: The Critical Drinker
description: Dwayne Johnson's had a tough time the past couple of years, but is The Smashing Machine, the story of real life MMA fighter Mark Kerr, going to be the start of his epic comeback? Find out in this review.
title: The Smashing Machine - A Knockout For The Rock?
